<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,610,956]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
The 
<typeStatus box="[251,302,650,676]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1844" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1844" box="[339,747,650,676]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Conops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipennis">
<emphasis box="[339,555,650,675]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Conops rufipennis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart" box="[561,747,650,676]" pageId="37" pageNumber="40" refString="Macquart, P. J. M. (1844). Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. Tom deuxiemme. 3. e partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences, de l'Agriculture et des Arts de Lille´42, 162 - 450." type="journal article" year="1844">
Macquart, 
<number box="[688,747,650,676]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" value="1844.0">1844</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was examined. The specimen does not fit in the concept of the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[313,506,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kroeberoconops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Camras" box="[515,680,690,716]" pageId="37" pageNumber="39" refString="Camras, S. (1955). A review of the New World flies of the genus Conops and allies (Diptera: Conopidae). Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 105, 155 - 187." type="journal article" year="1955">
Camras, 
<number box="[621,680,690,716]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" value="1955.0">1955</number>
</bibRefCitation>
because the flagellum is longer than the pedicel. The specimen belongs in the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[439,595,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pachyconops</emphasis>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[612,746,730,756]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">comb. nov.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,610,956]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
We haven’t seen Costa Rican specimens of this species so the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName box="[1121,1404,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipennis">
<emphasis box="[1121,1404,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Physoconops rufipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,278,810,836]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
remains doubtful.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,610,956]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
The subgenus 
<emphasis box="[377,570,850,875]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kroeberoconops</emphasis>
now only includes two species – 
<taxonomicName authority="Krober, 1915" authorityName="Krober" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hermanni" subGenus="Kroeberoconops">
<emphasis box="[996,1151,850,875]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Physoconops</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1172,1365,850,875]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kroeberoconops</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">hermanni</emphasis>
(Kröber, 
<number box="[340,400,890,916]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" value="1915.0">1915</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Camras, 2004" authorityName="Camras" authorityYear="2004" box="[467,1151,890,916]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Physoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentinus" subGenus="Kroeberoconops">
<emphasis box="[467,621,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Physoconops</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[640,833,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kroeberoconops</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[851,975,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">argentinus</emphasis>
Camras, 
<number box="[1089,1151,890,916]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</taxonomicName>
. The distribution of this subgenus is restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[441,557,930,956]" name="Argentina" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and it is unlikely that 
<emphasis box="[819,1012,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kroeberoconops</emphasis>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[1133,1266,930,956]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
